NPP Procurement Mentor
-
Date Posted: 2014/04/30 05:11:52
Ref. JB3045667
Job Description
*Nuclear power plant experience is mandatory - only candidates with the relevant experience will be considered for the role.
To provide regular oversight and coaching to employees during training and after assumption of their designated post.To manage procurement activities, particularly for nuclear-related materials, equipment and services, from initiation to post-award administration to ensure the requirements are met in a safe, compliant, timely, and efficient manner; to ensure consistency in application of procurement processes.
Mentoring
•Serve as a role model, confidant, coach and complimentary instructor to trainees in the training qualification program
•Monitor the performance of assigned mentees and take actions as deemed necessary to assist the mentees in the successful completion of the training or qualification program
•Meet regularly with mentees to collect feedback, assess progress, and formulate recommendations for improvement
•Document meetings, observations
•Provide frequent feedback to line management on trainee performance
•Escalate mentee critical performance issues or concerns to line and training management; consult with training, HR or senior management for advice and direction as required
•Oversee OJT sessions, and provide feedback on trainee performance and on the provider of the OJT
Procurement Management
•Supervise the work of the Specialists; approvals of their work in line with the DOA
•Ensure that at all stages of the procurement process, all Quality Assurance, HSE, Engineering, and end user requirements are included and the procurement is done in a compliant manner
•Interface with Engineering and QA as necessary to resolve issues
•Handle all aspects of high-value high-risk procurements, or any other procurements as directed by management
•Support the Procurement Supplier team in the qualification of nuclear suppliers
•Market research and analysis as required
•Assist in the development of procurement and supply chain strategies to ensure security of supply
•Lead the tendering process, including document preparation, negotiation
and acquiring
approvals
•Communicate and interface with
the end users, Engineering, Quality Assurance, and suppliers during tendering and post award in commercial and contractual matters
•Ensure a robust and commercially driven business case is prepared to support recommendations for award, proving assurance to management that the best agreement has been obtained
•Carry out some
contract administration functions and supervise the close out and feedback on performance
•Provide the necessary “checks and balances” oversight to ensure that supplier’s supply chain/procurement activities meet the contractual obligations of their contract
•Manage the close-out of agreements
•Lead negotiations with suppliers, if required
•Review and approve all Supplier invoices to ensure “work” billed is in accordance with the Purchase Order terms
Quality Assurance
•Ensure that all work carried out is of the highest standards of safety and quality, and in compliance with the department and company-wide quality assurance program, in order to effectively support safe and reliable plant operation
•Support continuous learning and application of industry best practices in order to maintain the highest quality of procurement workmanship
•Promptly report quality related issues or deficiencies on procurement activities to line management
Training and Qualifications
•Develop the appropriate training plans,
training materials,
and awareness
sessions
to ensure
team members receive necessary
training and skills required for
their development
•Keep current with Procurement best practices and update colleagues as applicable
••Strive to improve NPP technical knowledge level, understanding of overall plant operation and maintenance, and impact of procurement activities on safe, reliable and cost-effective operation and maintenance of NPP
Skills
Bachelor degree in Engineering
10 years nuclear power plant experience, in Supply Chain Management,
Procurement
Knowledge of nuclear quality standards
Knowledge of ASME standards
Knowledge of quality management systems
Strong commercial and contractual knowledge
Fluency in written and spoken English
Preferred:
Masters degree in a related field
MCIPS or other professional Procurement qualification
Mentoring or training experience
Engineering or Financial Background
Robust experience on a major ERP
Financial aspects in Contracts
Legal issues in Contracts
